'''Hamid Samandarian''' ([[Persian language|Persian ]]: <U+062D><U+0645><U+06CC><U+062F> <U+0633><U+0645><U+0646><U+062F><U+0631><U+06CC><U+0627><U+0646> - born [[1931]], died [[July 12]], [[2012]]) was an [[Iranian people|Iranian]] film and theater director and translator. <ref>{{cite web|title=Veteran Iranian director Hamid Samandarian dies at 81|url=http://www.ibna.ir/vdcc1iqs02bq0o8.-ya2.html}}</ref> He staged numerous dramas during his lifetime, including No Exit by [[Jean Paul Sartre]], [[Ghosts (play)|Ghosts]] by [[Henrik Ibsen]],[[The Glass Menagerie]] by [[Tennessee Williams]] and [[Marriage of Mr. Mississippi]] by [[Friedrich Durrenmatt]]. <ref>{{cite web|title=Veteran Iranian director Hamid Samandarian dies aged 81|url=http://vestnikkavkaza.net/news/culture/28909.html}}</ref> 

